===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|speken||to speak|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|specan|specan|to speak|lang=ang}}, alteration of earlier {{term|sprecan|sprecan|to speak|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*sprekaną||to speak, make a sound}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*spreg-||to make a sound, utter, speak}}. Cognate with West Frisian {{term|sprekke|lang=fy}}, Low German {{term|spreken||to speak|lang=nds}}, Dutch {{term|spreken||to speak|lang=nl}}, German {{term|sprechen||to speak|lang=de}}, and also with Albanian {{term|shpreh||to utter, voice, express|lang=sq}} through Indo-European.

